"# N+1 evaluations in Langfuse

Do you want to compare N model/prompt variants on the same dataset (A/B/N), each scored by one or more evaluators? And which SDK are you using (Python or JS/TS)?

## Pattern: A/B/N (N variants) on one dataset
Run one experiment per variant on the same dataset, attach identical evaluators, then compare runs in the UI.

_Prerequisites_
- Create/choose a dataset: see Datasets ([docs](https://langfuse.com/docs/evaluation/dataset-runs/datasets))

### Python (minimal)
_python_example.py_
```python
from langfuse import get_client, Evaluation

lf = get_client()
dataset = lf.get_dataset("my-eval-dataset")

def task(*, item, variant, **_):
    # call your app/model with the variant (prompt/model/params)
    # return plain output string/object
    return f"answer by {variant} to: {item['input']}"

def exact_match(*, input, output, expected_output, **_):
    v = 1.0 if expected_output and str(expected_output).lower() in str(output).lower() else 0.0
    return Evaluation(name="accuracy", value=v)

for variant in ["prompt_v1", "prompt_v2", "prompt_v3"]:
    result = dataset.run_experiment(
        name=f"abn-{variant}",
        description="A/B/N on same dataset",
        task=lambda *, item, **kw: task(item=item, variant=variant),
        evaluators=[exact_match],
        metadata={"variant": variant},
    )
    print(result.format())
```

### JS/TS (minimal)
_abn.ts_
```ts
import { LangfuseClient, ExperimentItem } from "@langfuse/client";

const lf = new LangfuseClient();
const dataset = await lf.dataset.get("my-eval-dataset");

const task = async (item: ExperimentItem, variant: string) => {
  return `answer by ${variant} to: ${item.input}`;
};

const accuracy = async ({ output, expectedOutput }: any) => ({
  name: "accuracy",
  value: expectedOutput && String(output).toLowerCase()
    .includes(String(expectedOutput).toLowerCase()) ? 1.0 : 0.0,
});

for (const variant of ["prompt_v1", "prompt_v2", "prompt_v3"]) {
  const res = await dataset.runExperiment({
    name: `abn-${variant}`,
    description: "A/B/N on same dataset",
    task: (item) => task(item, variant),
    evaluators: [accuracy],
    metadata: { variant },
  });
  console.log(await res.format());
}
```

- This creates N dataset runs that are directly comparable. See Remote Dataset Runs ([docs](https://langfuse.com/docs/evaluation/dataset-runs/remote-run)).

## Add an “+1” judge
Attach one or more LLM-as-a-judge or custom evaluators to all runs.

- Python evaluator example: [Evaluations (Python)](https://langfuse.com/docs/observability/sdk/python/evaluation)
- JS Autoevals integration: [Remote Runs → Autoevals](https://langfuse.com/docs/evaluation/dataset-runs/remote-run)

JS Autoevals (optional):
```ts
import { Factuality } from "autoevals";
import { createEvaluatorFromAutoevals } from "@langfuse/client";
const factuality = createEvaluatorFromAutoevals(Factuality());
/* pass evaluators: [factuality, ...] in runExperiment */
```

## Notes
- Running multiple predictions per item in a single run is not the recommended path; prefer one dataset run per variant and compare runs in the UI. The SDKs are built to “run multiple experiments on the same dataset in parallel” and attach the same evaluators for apples-to-apples comparison ([docs](https://langfuse.com/docs/evaluation/dataset-runs/remote-run)).

## Links
- Datasets: create and populate ([docs](https://langfuse.com/docs/evaluation/dataset-runs/datasets))
- Remote Dataset Runs and evaluators ([docs](https://langfuse.com/docs/evaluation/dataset-runs/remote-run))
- Python evaluations API ([docs](https://langfuse.com/docs/observability/sdk/python/evaluation))"

